      {
         "id": "introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nSince childhood, we have heard temporal expressions like: *\"the time is over\"*.\n\nOur relationship with time is so profound that it has inspired numerous popular sayings and poems, such as the following",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "201b48d7-ffdb-42f4-84d6-484a0bbe700e",
                     "text": "Rodrigues, W., Soares Filho, A. C., Vale, M. S. do, & Menezes, M. C.",
                     "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "2023", "month" : "-1", "day" : "-1" }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ":"
            },
            {
               "text": "<ul class=\"citation\"><li><i>Time asked Time:</i></li><li><i>\"What time does Time possess?\"</i></li><li><i>Time replied:</i></li><li><i> \"I have no time to say.</i></li><li><i>The time that remains within Time</i></li><li><i>is the time that is left to stay.\"</i></li><li><i> </i></li></ul>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": " "
            },
            {
               "text": "With this in mind, we propose an initial reflection",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ":"
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: On time</b><br /><br />What is time?</div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": " "
            }
         ]
      },
      {
          "id" : "perception",
          "text" : [ 
            { "text" : "### The Perception of Time\n\nWhen studying ancient texts, we observe that humanity has been analyzing time and its relationship with our lives for millennia. The first example used in History Tracers—and one of the oldest recorded—is the **Sumerian King List**",
              "source" : [
                           { "type": 0,
                             "uuid": "4d0b579d-57af-45e1-87b0-d402dd778968",
                             "text": "Sumerian King List"}
              ],
              "isTable" : false,
              "date_time" : null,
              "format" : "markdown",
              "PostMention": "."
            },
            { "text" : "<p class=\"desc\"><img src=\"images/Ashmolean/KingList.jpg\" id=\"imgKL\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgKL', '0%')\" class=\"imgcenter\"/>Figure 1: Sumerian King List. © Ashmolean Museum, University of Oxford (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillPrimarySource('4d0b579d-57af-45e1-87b0-d402dd778968'); return false;\">Ashmolean Image Library</a>)</p>",
              "source" : null,
              "isTable" : false,
              "date_time" : null,
              "format" : "html",
              "PostMention": " "
            },
            { "text" : "While the text includes implausible lifespans for humans, such as Enmenluana’s 43,200-year reign, it also provides more detailed records, like En-tarah-ana’s reign: 420 years…, 3 months, and 3 and 1/2 days. In both cases, we see the concept of cyclical time",
              "source" : [
                           { "type": 1,
                             "uuid": "cb216fdf-1282-42e0-aaf4-3547b53857d7",
                             "text": "Black, J.A., et. al., ln. 11 - 12, 50 - 51",
                             "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "1998", "month" : "-1", "day" : "-1" }},
                           { "type": 1,
                             "uuid": "c8dd380c-6f66-415c-94fa-b116308adeef",
                             "text": "Black, J.A., et. al. (Traducción)",
                             "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "1998", "month" : "-1", "day" : "-1" }},
                           { "type": 0,
                             "uuid": "4d0b579d-57af-45e1-87b0-d402dd778968",
                             "text": "Lista de los Reyes Sumérios"}
              ],
              "isTable" : false,
              "date_time" : null,
              "format" : "markdown",
              "PostMention": " "
            },
            { "text" : "In ancient Jewish texts, particularly the Book of Ecclesiastes, we encounter a similar periodic view of time",
              "source" : [
                           { "type": 2,
                             "uuid": "56e19b6d-5b12-4a9d-abff-7c85ff465872",
                             "text": "Torah, Neviim u-Khetuvim. Twenty-four books of the Holy Scriptures carefully translated according to the Massoretic text, on the basis of the English version, after the best Jewish authorities, Capítulo 3, pp. 876",
                             "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "1998", "month" : "-1", "day" : "-1" }}
              ],
              "isTable" : false,
              "date_time" : null,
              "format" : "markdown",
              "PostMention": " "
            },
            { "text" : "<ul class=\"citation\"><li><i>For every thing there is a season; and a (proper) time is for every pursuit under the heavens.....</li></ul>",
              "source" : null,
              "isTable" : false,
              "date_time" : null,
              "format" : "html",
              "PostMention": " "
            },
            { "text" : "This cyclical perception of time is not limited to written records. In Mesoamerica, for instance, Type E structures were likely tied to temporal events like harvests, hunts, and seasonal changes",
              "source" : [
                           { "type": 1,
                             "uuid": "e7c7458b-0c63-4485-9c7b-4640edcd9122",
                             "text": "Inomata, T.",
                             "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "2017", "month" : "-1", "day" : "-1" }}
              ],
              "isTable" : false,
              "date_time" : null,
              "format" : "markdown",
              "PostMention": "."
            },
            { "text" : "<p class=\"desc\"><iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/UBMUR-3hHz0?si=mn22_mrWLJ23ueeO\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe><br />Video 1: Type E at Caracol, Belize. Recorded during a site visit on <htdate0>.</p>",
              "source" : null,
              "isTable" : false,
              "date_time" : [
                    {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "2015", "month" : "4", "day" : "26" }
              ],
              "format" : "html",
              "PostMention": " "
            },
            { "text" : "The same concept appears in the Mesoamerican Ballgame, as noted in the First Steps section. Research by scholars like Aguilar-Moreno suggests this ceremonial space was directly linked to day and night, reflecting an understanding of solar movement",
              "source" : [
                           { "type": 1,
                             "uuid": "87a40e3a-c09b-466a-8a15-37091ddd38a5",
                             "text": "Aguilar-Moreno, M.",
                             "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "2015", "month" : "-1", "day" : "-1" }}
              ],
              "isTable" : false,
              "date_time" : null,
              "format" : "markdown",
              "PostMention": "."
            },
            { "text" : "<p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"Copan\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('Copan', '0%')\" src=\"images/Copan/JuegoDePelotaCopan.jpg\" class=\"imgcenter\"/>Figure 2: The Ballgame Court at Copán, Honduras. Photographed on <htdate0> during a site visit.</p>",
               "source" : null,
               "isTable" : false,
               "date_time" : [
                    {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "2015", "month" : "4", "day" : "26" }
               ],
               "format" : "html",
               "PostMention": " "
             },
            { "text" : "Yet this perception does not define time itself. Let us now proceed to the next section to explore this further",
              "source" : null,
              "isTable" : false,
              "date_time" : null,
              "format" : "markdown",
              "PostMention": "."
            }
          ]
      }
